<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sayleth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know that Specializing reduces mana costs of associated spells.  That is about all I know, however.<P>How many specializations do you get?  From the look on the guild trainer screen, more than one.<P>What happens when you are 20+ and train a specialization, does it bring up a dialog box to pick a spell type?  What happens from there?  Can you specialize more than once in the same spell type for more benefit?<P>Finally, I would like to hear thoughts on what are best magics to specialize in.<P>Thanks<P>Sayleth</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Talis Et'Souls</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Firstly, I would suggest before posting stuff you look further down the list, you will find many posts asking the same questions.<P>Ok, you get specialize in all 5 disciplines of spells but there is only one that you can take past skill level of 50. The usual for Necromancers is Alteration.<P>At level 20 I just put 1 point into each specialization skill, they will go up as you use each type of spell but the first to hit 51 will be the one you will the bonuses for. It will go up to 150 max and the others will stay at 50. You start your specialization in each one at the level you put the pracs into it.<P>Because I used Alteration for most spells at level 20+ it hit 51 first easily. Some say to just put the point into the one you want to speciazlize in then wait for it to hit a decent level but I would suggest don't bother, you by far use Alteration the most at that level so it will go up fast.<P>You will see messages such as:<P>You have become better at Specialize Alteration skill! (51) etc that is the messages you are looking for.<P>In the skills list there is some confusion as they all just say "Specialize" in the box. You can tell which is which by going down in Alpha order i.e. Abjuration, Alteration, Conjuration, Divination, Evocation.<P>Regards,<P>------------------<BR><B>Talis Et'Souls<BR>Lanys T'Vyl Server<P>"You could rip my heart out"  *grins evilly*  "If I had one."</B></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sayleth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks.  It would seem like Alteration is the way to go for a Necro.<P>Sayleth</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bezel Ubub</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Specialization question What does this really do does it mean i can cast these spell types while running or getting hit easyier or what I did choose Alteration but I dont know what the benefit is of Specialization?<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Azkirte</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The spells you cast will sometimes cost less mana.  There's also less of a chance of fizzling.  I'm not sure if it will help with interrupts or not.  I think that is a strictly channeling issue.<P>------------------<BR>Azkirte Gix<P>"Just remember I will always love you, Even as I tear your fucking throat away."</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kierlak</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually Talis, specialization will go higher than 150.  <P>I am positive that my Spec: Alteration just hit 191 the other day.  I had just made 39 and was a bit alarmed to think that my alteration skill was only just now reaching 191, at 38 it should have been maxxed at 195, so I went back and re-read the message.  <P>Sure enough it said:<BR>   You have become better at Specialize Alteration (191)!<P>Not sure what the final cap is, but it is sloooow between increases.  I hadn't seen a bump in spec: alter since long before that one.<P>Kierlak SoulReaver</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
